---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Solutions &mdash; Forge T Labs"
  description="Packaged ISV solutions from Forge T Labs, built on the Microsoft Cloud to extend Dynamics 365 and Microsoft 365."
  canonical=""
  ogType="website"
  active="Solutions"
>
<main id="top">
<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="hero-glow"></div>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> &nbsp;/&nbsp; Solutions</div>
    <h1>Software for the <em>built environment</em>.</h1>
    <p class="lede">Forge T Labs builds a family of products that follow a building through its
      whole life &mdash; design, construction, operation and ownership. Each one is a packaged
      ISV solution, engineered natively on Dynamics 365 and the Microsoft Cloud, so your projects,
      properties and people share one data model instead of a dozen disconnected tools.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- LIFECYCLE INTRO -->
<section>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head reveal">
      <span class="mono">The product family</span>
      <h2>One platform across the <em>building lifecycle</em>.</h2>
      <p>Most teams manage the built environment with a patchwork of disconnected tools &mdash; one
        for the design brief, another for the build, a third for operations, a spreadsheet for the
        portfolio. Forge T Labs builds four products that share a single Microsoft Cloud data
        model, so a building stays connected from first design brief to long-term asset.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step reveal"><div class="sn">STAGE 01</div>
        <h4>Spec it</h4><p>SpecForge captures the workplace design brief and requirements before drawings begin.</p></div>
      <div class="step reveal"><div class="sn">STAGE 02</div>
        <h4>Build it</h4><p>BuildForge runs the construction project through to handover.</p></div>
      <div class="step reveal"><div class="sn">STAGE 03</div>
        <h4>Operate it</h4><p>SiteForge keeps the occupied building running day to day.</p></div>
      <div class="step reveal"><div class="sn">STAGE 04</div>
        <h4>Own it</h4><p>AssetForge tracks the building as a long-term real estate asset.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- PRODUCT GRID -->
<section class="band">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head reveal">
      <span class="mono">Our products</span>
      <h2>Four products, <em>one</em> connected suite.</h2>
      <p>Each product solves a stage of the building lifecycle and works on its own &mdash; or
        together as a single platform. Every one is engineered natively on Dynamics 365 and the
        Microsoft Cloud.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="product-grid">

      <!-- BUILDFORGE -->
      <article class="product reveal">
        <div class="phead">
          <div class="picon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="1.6">
            <path d="M3 21h18M6 21V8l6-4 6 4v13"/><path d="M10 21v-5h4v5" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></div>
          <div><div class="stage">Stage 02 &middot; Build it</div>
            <h3>BuildForge</h3></div>
        </div>
        <div class="ptag">Run every project from groundbreaking to handover.</div>
        <p class="pdesc">Construction project management for contractors and builders who already
          work in Microsoft 365. Track projects, budgets, RFIs, submittals and change orders in one
          place &mdash; with budget-vs-actual that updates as the job moves.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 8.5l3.5 3.5 6.5-7"/></svg>Project, phase &amp; milestone tracking</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 8.5l3.5 3.5 6.5-7"/></svg>RFI and submittal logs</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 8.5l3.5 3.5 6.5-7"/></svg>Change orders with budget-vs-actual costing</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 8.5l3.5 3.5 6.5-7"/></svg>Document &amp; drawing register</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 8.5l3.5 3.5 6.5-7"/></svg>Subcontractor coordination</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="pfor"><b>For:</b> General contractors &amp; construction firms</div>
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="contact.html?product=BuildForge">Enquire about BuildForge &rarr;</a>
      </article>

      <!-- SITEFORGE -->
      <article class="product reveal">
        <div class="phead">
          <div class="picon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="1.6">
            <path d="M3 21h18M5 21V7l7-4 7 4v14"/><path d="M9 9h2M13 9h2M9 13h2M13 13h2M9 17h6" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></div>
          <div><div class="stage">Stage 03 &middot; Operate it</div>
            <h3>SiteForge</h3></div>
        </div>
        <div class="ptag">Keep every building running, tenant-ready and compliant.</div>
        <p class="pdesc">Property operations for managers and facilities teams responsible for
          occupied buildings. Handle work orders, preventive maintenance, inspections and tenant
          requests, and keep vendors and compliance on track &mdash; across one building or a
          whole portfolio.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 8.5l3.5 3.5 6.5-7"/></svg>Work-order management</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 8.5l3.5 3.5 6.5-7"/></svg>Preventive maintenance scheduling</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 8.5l3.5 3.5 6.5-7"/></svg>Inspection &amp; compliance tracking</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 8.5l3.5 3.5 6.5-7"/></svg>Tenant/occupant request portal</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 8.5l3.5 3.5 6.5-7"/></svg>Vendor coordination &amp; asset registers</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="pfor"><b>For:</b> Property managers &amp; facilities teams</div>
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="contact.html?product=SiteForge">Enquire about SiteForge &rarr;</a>
      </article>

      <!-- SPECFORGE -->
      <article class="product reveal">
        <div class="phead">
          <div class="picon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="1.6">
            <rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/><path d="M3 9h18M9 21V9" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></div>
          <div><div class="stage">Stage 01 &middot; Spec it</div>
            <h3>SpecForge</h3></div>
        </div>
        <div class="ptag">Turn workplace requirements into a build-ready spec.</div>
        <p class="pdesc">The requirements phase of an office fit-out, structured. Capture space
          programming, finish schedules, furniture and equipment specs and adjacency needs &mdash;
          the brief that goes to architects and contractors &mdash; without the usual sprawl of
          spreadsheets and email threads.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 8.5l3.5 3.5 6.5-7"/></svg>Space programming &amp; area schedules</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 8.5l3.5 3.5 6.5-7"/></svg>Finish &amp; material specifications</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 8.5l3.5 3.5 6.5-7"/></svg>Furniture/equipment (FF&amp;E) schedules</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 8.5l3.5 3.5 6.5-7"/></svg>Departmental adjacency planning</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 8.5l3.5 3.5 6.5-7"/></svg>Stakeholder sign-off &amp; handover pack</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="pfor"><b>For:</b> Corporate real estate &amp; design firms</div>
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="contact.html?product=SpecForge">Enquire about SpecForge &rarr;</a>
      </article>

      <!-- ASSETFORGE -->
      <article class="product reveal">
        <div class="phead">
          <div class="picon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="1.6">
            <path d="M3 21h18M5 21V11M12 21V7M19 21V13" stroke-linecap="round"/><path d="M4 8l7-4 8 5" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></div>
          <div><div class="stage">Stage 04 &middot; Own it</div>
            <h3>AssetForge</h3></div>
        </div>
        <div class="ptag">See your whole property portfolio in one view.</div>
        <p class="pdesc">Portfolio and asset tracking for commercial real estate owners and
          investors. Hold every property, lease, valuation and key date in one record, with the
          performance picture across the portfolio &mdash; so renewals, reviews and reporting never
          depend on someone's spreadsheet.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 8.5l3.5 3.5 6.5-7"/></svg>Property &amp; asset register</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 8.5l3.5 3.5 6.5-7"/></svg>Lease &amp; tenancy tracking</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 8.5l3.5 3.5 6.5-7"/></svg>Key-date &amp; renewal alerts</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 8.5l3.5 3.5 6.5-7"/></svg>Valuation &amp; performance history</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 8.5l3.5 3.5 6.5-7"/></svg>Portfolio dashboards &amp; reporting</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="pfor"><b>For:</b> CRE investors, asset managers &amp; owners</div>
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="contact.html?product=AssetForge">Enquire about AssetForge &rarr;</a>
      </article>

    </div>
    <p class="placeholder-note" style="margin-top:24px">&#8627; Feature lists are a first draft &mdash; refine against each product's real roadmap.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- WHY THE SUITE -->
<section>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head reveal">
      <span class="mono">Why one suite</span>
      <h2>The building doesn't start over &mdash; <em>your data shouldn't either</em>.</h2>
      <p>Because all four products share one Microsoft Cloud data model, a building carries its
        history with it from stage to stage.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pillars">
      <article class="pillar reveal">
        <span class="num">/ 01</span>
        <div class="ic"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="1.6">
          <path d="M7 8h10M7 12h10M7 16h6" stroke-linecap="round"/><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Shared data model</h3>
        <p>A SpecForge fit-out brief becomes a BuildForge project; the finished building flows into
          SiteForge and AssetForge &mdash; no re-keying, no export/import.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="pillar reveal">
        <span class="num">/ 02</span>
        <div class="ic"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="1.6">
          <path d="M12 2 3 7v10l9 5 9-5V7l-9-5Z"/><path d="M12 22V12M3 7l9 5 9-5" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Native to Microsoft</h3>
        <p>Built on Dynamics 365 and Dataverse, secured by your own tenant and identity &mdash; and
          ready to pair with Microsoft 365 and Copilot.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="pillar reveal">
        <span class="num">/ 03</span>
        <div class="ic"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#3fc878" stroke-width="1.6">
          <path d="M3 7h18M3 7l3-4h12l3 4M5 7v13a1 1 0 0 0 1 1h12a1 1 0 0 0 1-1V7" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Adopt one or all</h3>
        <p>Start with the product that solves today's problem. Add the others when you're ready
          &mdash; they connect automatically, with no migration project.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="band">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head reveal">
      <span class="mono">Questions</span>
      <h2>Things customers <em>ask us</em>.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq reveal">
      <details>
        <summary>Can we buy just one product? <span class="pm">+</span></summary>
        <p>Yes. Each product stands on its own and solves a complete stage of the building
          lifecycle. The suite is the advantage when you run more than one &mdash; but it is never
          a requirement.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Where does the software run? <span class="pm">+</span></summary>
        <p>All four products are built natively on Microsoft Dynamics 365 and the Power Platform,
          and deploy into your own Microsoft tenant. Your data stays within your tenant boundary
          and security model.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Do we need an existing Dynamics 365 or Microsoft 365 tenant? <span class="pm">+</span></summary>
        <p>A Microsoft tenant is required, since the products extend the Microsoft Cloud. If you
          don't have one yet, our Dynamics 365 and Modern Work services can set that up first.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How do the products connect to each other? <span class="pm">+</span></summary>
        <p>They share a single Dataverse data model. A design brief, a construction project, an
          operating building and a portfolio asset are the same underlying records &mdash; so
          information moves between stages with no re-entry.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How is it licensed and priced? <span class="pm">+</span></summary>
        <p>Per user, on a monthly or annual subscription, per product. Send us an enquiry below and
          we'll put together pricing for the products and team size you need.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CTA -->
<section style="padding-top:40px">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="cta-band reveal">
      <div class="glow"></div>
      <h2>Find the right product for your team.</h2>
      <p>Tell us which stage of the building lifecycle you're working on and we'll show you the
        product that fits &mdash; and how it works in your Microsoft environment.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact">Submit an enquiry &rarr;</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="index.html#services">Explore our services</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
</main>
</BaseLayout>
